<title>SPAIN: Mexico plans to launch two-yr CETES in H2.</title>
<headline>Mexico plans to launch two-yr CETES in H2.</headline>
<dateline>BARCELONA, Spain 1997-03-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Undersecretary of Finance Martin Werner said on Monday that Mexico planned to launch two-year fixed-rate CETES in the second half of the year.</p>
<p>&quot;We hope to introduce two-year paper in CETES as inflation comes down and we hope in the next two years to introduce five-year paper,&quot; Werner told journalists before the start of the 38th annual meeting of the Inter-American Development Bank.</p>
